    {
      "id": "0736e27f18cd2a25841f9570b05ee5d145eec81c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 116,
        "name": "Brian J. Murrell",
        "email": "brian.murrell@intel.com",
        "username": "brian",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2011-08-08 14:43:22.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nChristopher,\n\nYour last comment in the changelog entry gives me concern.\n\nIMHO, if a source file (i.e. [parser|platform].h) is modified any targets that depend on it need to be rebuilt by make.\n\nI could imagine the level of frustration (and waste of time) it could lead some developer some day to be making changes to those files and not seeing those changes reflected in the result, leading him to have to debug the Makefiles only to figure out that \"make\" doesn't really make everything.\n\nIs that situation really not resolvable?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "eb84c257ed3270393d7a33f8606f1cbef8b1700c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 109,
        "name": "Christopher J. Morrone",
        "email": "morrone2@llnl.gov",
        "username": "morrone"
      },
      "date": "2011-08-08 14:56:20.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nWe are not breaking anything here, we are just removing entries that already do not work.\n\nThis is certainly fixable, but is really beyond the scope of this this patch.  This is also likely a larger problem in the lustre code base, not isolated to these two headers.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "fcbaeb08c876b9c47c1097bd2be4b1dda4ecb361",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 116,
        "name": "Brian J. Murrell",
        "email": "brian.murrell@intel.com",
        "username": "brian",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2011-08-08 15:21:14.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nCan you please file a JIRA ticket about the [parser|platform].h -> libcfsutil.a make dependency problem just so it doesn't get lost?  Thanx.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "94b0c1a98da87c38eca430a2482b64670b5b57cc",
      "author": {
